{"word":"ὀρεύς","slug":"ὀρεύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n74889\" key=\"o)reu/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὀρεύς</orth>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ion.\">Ion.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">οὐρεύς</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">έως</itype><foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">, ὁ</foreign> (even <sense id=\"n74889.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὁ θῆλυς ὀ.</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg014:577b:22\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arist.\">Arist.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ HA\">HA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">577b22</biblScope></bibl></cit>, though <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τῆς θηλείας</foreign> follows <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τοῖς θήλεσιν</foreign> ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0086.tlg014:573a:16\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">573a16</biblScope> </bibl>), <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">mule,</tr_> in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author></bibl>, as a beast of draught and burden, always in <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ion.\">Ion.</a></gram> </gramGrp> form, synon. with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἡμίονος,</foreign> cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:23:115\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.115</biblScope> </bibl> with <bibl n=\"u